			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Today NaCl in Chrome supports NPAPI but not Pepper2. While it is desirable to keep NPAPI for testing purposes, we don't want to expose it to external developers.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
We need to avoid exposing interfaces like NPAPI that are not meant for use by external developers.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
NaCl should support a build flag that makes NPAPI support a build-time option.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Release build of Chrome with NaCl does not support NPAPI interfaces.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Developers won't be able to use NPAPI with NaCl.
